Remington 'Remi' Walden, of Bainbridge, Georgia, was killed when his family's Jeep Grand Cherokee was hit from behind by a pickup truck in March 2012 .
The fuel tank leaked, engulfing the Jeep in flames and killing the four-year-old boy .
A jury of 11 women and one man ruled that Chrysler was 99 per cent at fault for the crash and the pickup driver was 1 per cent .
It is not the largest judgment ever against an automaker in a personal injury case .